    "body": "Ok, will try few times more and wait longer, I didn't wait so long, usually up to 10 minutes, but was trying many times these days in different parts of the day. \r\n\r\nI'm thinking now even I manage to catch that bug, there is a qt class which provides an interface for receiving native events but even then at least part of the fix need to be handled in OS' native code. Some idea may be to handle for macOS system notification kIOMessageSystemWillSleep and do some checks before system go to sleep state, and handle kIOMessageSystemWillPowerOn notification to prepare the app and reset its data once system is back from the sleep state.  That way, I guess, we will have all messages, transactions correctly displayed and not miss any if it has happened while system was in a sleep state (the app was inactive).\r\n\r\nBut I am not sure is this completely possible in nim, maybe we should try, all in all this should be discussed before we start. \r\n@iurimatias any thoughts on this?",
